      <hedline>
        <hl1>Summertime Dues</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Angelica Veitch letter on Walter Kirn's July 9 Way We Life Now essay recalls being terrified by owner of fish-fry restaurant in Vermont where she worked as teen</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Walter Kirn's article reminded me of my first job, at age 14, at a fish-fry restaurant in Vermont. We were terrified of the owner, so rather than face his wrath when any food items dropped on the floor, we quickly returned them to their original places. I learned a valuable lesson from this experience: don't eat at fast-food places.</p>
        <p>Angelica Veitch  Baton Rouge, La.</p>
      </block>
